<dl id="n12031d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12031d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12031d"> 31(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ Ferre noctuam Athenas / owls to Athens ~ <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n12031d"><li>FW 120.20 </li><li><a href="../../flex/e/lexe.htm#n12031d">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/e/l39e.htm#n12031d">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n12031d">MS BL 47473-36v</ms> </li><li>JJA 46:332 <a name="ed3" href="../../ff/fdra/eda.htm#ed3">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/e/ed3.htm#n12031d">Draft: I.5&sect;1.3</a>/4.3</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">&hellip; Pour les profanes, la coque n&apos;est qu&apos;un petit mollusque, form&eacute; de deux valves sym&eacute;triques &eacute;galement bomb&eacute;es. Elle abonde dans les estuaires des petits fleuves bretons et normands, &agrave; 1'embouchure de la Vilaine, dans l&apos;anse de la Fresnaye, sous le cap Fr&eacute;hel et, surtout, dans la baie du Mont-Saint-Michel. De cette abondance est n&eacute; ce proverbe qui signifie faire une chose inutile: &ldquo;C&apos;est porter des coquilles &agrave; Saint-Michel&rdquo;, c&apos;est porter de l&apos;eau &agrave; la rivi&egrave;re et des chouettes &agrave; Ath&egrave;nes: Ferre noctuam Athenas. <br><font color="green">[For the profane among us, the cockle is no more than a humble mollusk, formed by two symmetrical valves. They are everywhere in the estuaries of the little Breton and Normand rivers, in the delta of the Vilaine, in the cove of Fresnaye, under cape Frehel and, especially, in the bay of Mont-Saint-Michel. Of this abundance a proverb was born that means doing something useless: &ldquo;To carry cockles to Saint-Michel&rdquo;, it is like carrying water to the river or <mark>owls to Athens. <i>Ferre noctuam Athenas</i></mark>.]</font> <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="LMSM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LMSM"><cite title="source">Les l&eacute;gendes du Mont-Saint-Michel</cite></a> (1924) 138-9</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
